    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1908-12-29T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1908-12-29T00:00:00-05:00" n="470"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d470">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 17172/2A.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">President <persName type="from">Roosevelt</persName> to the
                            <gloss type="to">King of Italy</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1908-12-29">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 29, 1908</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>With all my countrymen, I am appalled by the dreadful calamity which has befallen
                    your country. I offer my sincerest sympathy. American National Red Cross has
                    issued appeal for contributions for the sufferers and notified me that they will
                    immediately communicate with the Italian Red Cross.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Theodore Roosevelt.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
